com.obdobion.argument.input

Class CommandLineParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.obdobion.argument.input.AbstractInputParser
      • com.obdobion.argument.input.CommandLineParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParserInput

    public class CommandLineParser
extends AbstractInputParser
implements IParserInput
    This parser takes a typical command line entry and creates tokens. A command line is made up of key words and values. A key word is prefixed by a - or two. Brackets or parenthesis may be used to create subparsers.
    Author:
    Chris DeGreef fedupforone@gmail.com
